< Text>
There is a young female employ a couple days ago, who went out of her way to make sure we had everything we ordered. More than enough sauce, and even bags and drink holders to carry the food to the car with. I was honestly blown away with how much of an effort she put in to help us. She deserves 5 stars.

Unfortunately me and my wife ordered again tonight, mainly because we were so impressed with the previous employees work ethic.  However upon  entering the store I was helped by a young-ish male "shift lead" who made absolutely no effort, in any way, to make our experience pleasant, let alone barrable. We had two online orders, I explained to him that my wife had forgot to upgrade the standard medium drinks to large drinks. Before I could even finish asking to pay the difference he threw his hands in the air and said "sorry I have no control over the app there's nothing I can do."

I then offered to pay the difference so that we could upgrade the drinks and he flat out said no, then walked away when I told him I wanted to place a separate order. He ignored me, and made me wait to order until our online orders were already ready. So our food just sat there getting cold while I finally ordered, than waited another 5 more minutes for a taco and a bean burrito.

I asked if there was anyone that I could speak to about paying to upgrade the drinks and he again just said "I am the manager, there's nothing I can do." He made no effort to try to make something work. I wasn't asking for free upgrades I asked multiple times if I could pay. I hope the 40 cents that he wouldn't let me pay to upgrade our drinks was worth losing out on a faithful customers business.< /Text>

< Text>
I have been a Mytee customer for over 5 years straight now.  I am an owner operator of a successful carpet cleaning business located in Los Angeles, Ca.
When I first started out my business I purchased a Mytee M5, and soon added an Air Hog, Air Hog Plus, T Rex, Stair wands, wands, burnisher, and many more Mytee Products.
I chose Mytee because of the looks and price point. Till this day I still use my Mytee M5 portable in my Rug Shop.  It still has the original motors in it too after all these years.
Over the 5 years I've been doing business with Mytee they have continually updated their equipment.  When they do they notify me and send me the updated parts at no cost.
Any time I've had any problems or questions Mytee has stepped up to the place and immediately remedied the situation.  Even when it was not their  fault but mine due to abuse or ignorance.
Mytee has the best customer service of any company out there that I've dealt with and I have dealt with many. Which is the reason why I am writing this review.  I noticed how some have claimed the opposite.  I can only assume the posters have ulterior motives.  Because if anything, Mytee is all about customer service.  No one can hold a candle to them and that is the truth.  Thanks Mytee for the many years of great service.< /Text>

<name>Joe Anstead< /name>< review>
To Mytee Products,
Wanted to let You know how an service employee of yours handled
a mix up in part ordering. The Techs name is Chery LaRue.
I got the wrong gasket for My 20 year old machine. I was worried that
You would not carry the gasket anymore because the machine was so old.(It still works like a champ!) Any way Ms. Larue checked and rechecked and found the correct gasket replacement part that had changed over the years and informed Me they would ship the
part at no charge to Me. I think that is fair and a good service practice.
Its GREAT to see this kind of service. Ms. Larue did a good job
and I am grateful.
After 20 Years My Machine and Your Service are Still MYTEE !
Thanks,
Joe
EDIT:
In the end, well after My 1st review, Mytee got my money and
I never did get the right part or my money back. They sent 2 wrong parts and the customer support service is set up in such a way that you will not get your money back. Very clever.
A MYTEE RIP OFF.
I want to say it was not  for lack of trying by the service tech.
The truth is mytee has my money and I got nothing.

<Response>None< /Response>< Text>
Recently bought LDT 3 from these guys.  The machine has a lot of features that I find very useful for my business, however almost immediately I ran into a large problem.  The extractor has an auto fill feature.  You can connect a hose to the machine and it will automatically fill the fresh water tank.  The first time I used this feature one of the internal hoses that Mytee installed blew apart.  I have pictures to prove it.  I understand that things can happen during fabrication, but this was pretty bad.  It got all of the components inside the machine soaked with water.

I took the machine back to the distributor to get fixed.  That was two weeks ago.  The distributor has been calling them every day to get a new hose to replace the broken one.  Mytee cannot find a part number for the hose, and is seems no one who works there is able to walk from the office to the fabrication floor, pick up a new hose and mail it.  Now they are simply inquiring the distributor's calls.

I would warn anyone who is thinking about buying a product form Mytee to seriously reconsider.  As far as I have seen they do not stand behind their products.  If something breaks or is defective you are pretty much on your own.</Text>

I am giving them 1 star, due to the fact that the office is probably the nicest and cleanest doctor's office in all of San Bernardino. I would give zero stars, if I could, for quality of care.  First off, the appointment staff is very rude and unprofessional. Some of the nurses at the office need an attitude adjustment. Some, not all! The doctor that I saw made me feel like I had to choose which one of my disorders did I want treated. My asthma, my pain or my anxiety? Um, how about treating them all?... And if you couldn't, why not refer me to someone/people who could? I was supposed to have a lung function test and was told by the rude check out clerk, I COULD NOT come back until it was done. Bottom line, this office and especially Dr. Lucas, need a LOT of help and professional training. Just because you have a nice office, doesn't mean you can skimp out on quality of care.

UPDATE:
I gave them another chance to help me.
First of all, I got my authorization for my lung function test, AFTER I wrote my first review. Coincidence? Probably not. . .

< review>
My husband and I have very different opinions on how the meal was so ill list both

I chose the 3 stars but my husband said only 1 star.

When we got there we observed only about 3 tables being used. Im not sure if they had just finished with a rush or not but all the other open tables were still dirty. They quickly cleared one off for us. Next when we went to order drinks, we were informed that their soda fountain doesn't work. I ordered a lemonade which was good. My husband after not being able to order the soda, then tried to order a drink to which he was told would have to be asked about. He was then informed they were out of that drink as well. He settled for a bottled coke.

When we went to order food everything went well at first. I ordered a grilled Burrito, my husband a chimichanga, and we got chicken strips for our son. About the time they were bringing mine and my sons meal out the waitress comes over asking my husband what type of meat he wanted in the chimichanga after already specificying the beef chimicanga. Mind you my sons meal and my meal are now sitting on the table after we have been waiting 30 minutes and only now are they confirming the meat in my husbands meal.

So we get our food. I have no complaints on my Burrito and my son seemed to love his food since he chowed down but my husband said the chimichanga didn't taste right at all. He ended up not eating it all and instead ate the rest of our sons meal.

Service seemed a bit slow at times but overall was decent. My experience varied differently from my husbands and, while I would consider coming back, my husband has said unfortunately he WOULD NOT reccomend this place and will not come back. I'm not sure if I would highly recommend this place to my friends either. I would definitely give ample warning to be prepared to have some issues and for them to be out of things but for the food to be good at least.< /review>

<user>102750469251893837932<//user><name>Justin Jardin< /name><Time>1499210869964</Time><Rating>5<//Rating><Review>A perfect Gem of a breakfast joint. Family owned and operated. The best option in town when it comes to traditional Mexican breakfast, lunch, and dinner dishes. They also happen to nail American and Continental style breakfast as well. I've cleared about half the menu, and have yet to encounter a dish that has come up short. The Head Chef is the Co-owner I believe along with the Husband who works as Host and waiter. Both of them are extremely personable and friendly and remember repeat and loyal customers. I recommend this place to anyone who even utters the word breakfast around me. Their lunch and dinner options are both delicious and more than reasonably priced. The one thing that could be construed as a down side is the size of the restaurant, but I see the small size as a pro not a con. It allows the staff to interact with their patrons on an intimate level and lends itself to the home style menu. A must visit for anyone even remotely near the Santa Clarita Valley.<//Review><Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMLnZhhhATBPFqn-41B2VC5RhAD3K3qHWEArsQ0=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pics><Response>None<//Response><Gmap_id>0x80c288ea0b6bf801:0x46533211f40fef30<//Gmap_id></record>

<Review>As the last reviewer stated, at first you don't expect much from its location. However, this turned out to be one one the best Mexican meals I've had outside of Mexico itself. Parking is very easy and the restaurant sits about 30 or so. The manager is very friendly and is concerned about how you like your meal. I had the cochinito pibil (a specialty from the Yucatan) for about $11. The taste was excellent and it came with the standard-beans, Spanish rice, and tortillas. I will certainly be back again and again.<//Review>< user_id>

<text>I have a new favorite place to eat in Santa Clarita. I was impressed by the decor when I first walked in the door. Very creative use of space and nicely decorated interior. I moved to the patio as it was very nicely appointed as well. The staff was very friendly and I felt comfortable immediately. The service is outstanding and when our meals came I was very pleasantly surprised. Delicious food served in beautiful white dishes. The presentation of the food matched the flavor and I am now hooked on this restaurant. I am very particular about Menudo and this was the best I ever had, fresh, hot and flavorful. The chicken mole, which is prepared with a tender breast and delicious sauce was a work of art. Try the desserts, you won't be disappointed. This was my first visit and I am looking forward to working my way through the menu. The owners are very friendly and charming. Give this place a try if you are tired of factory food. Dining should be an experience and this place does not disappoint.</text><rate>5<//rate>< Time>

< review>
We decided with over 400 restaurants in the Santa Clarita Valley, we needed to start spreading our wings and start trying more of them. So we picked Ay Caramba! based on the favorable Trip Advisor reviews. Wow! What a find!! We went for a late lunch/early dinner at 2:30 p.m. and had the place all to ourselves. The owner and his wife (I assume it was his wife since this is a family owned and operator restaurant) were both very charming and amiable. We had fun conversing with them and they delighted in our raving over the excellent food. I feel so bad for my regular Mexican food haunts as they will be seeing less of me as I come back to Ay Caramba! to try more of their dishes. Today I had the Pipian made with a rather huge chicken breast.< /review>

<rating>4< /rating>< review>
Small place with lots of Goodness. We ate outside, It is very beautifully decorated and feels homie. You can hear the water fountain in the background and feel the breeze as you enjoy your amazing food.

Mexican food on point. We had four dishes served. Everything from the Waitress attending to us, to the food was perfect!

My girlfriend had the Chicken enchiladas, and she enjoy how delicious and good it was.
She also had the Shreded Beef Mojado Burrito .. and she said the sauce on it was perfect.. not spicy but good and perfect.

4 star for the food.
Had the Grilled Steak Burrito and it was delightful and big.

The location is small but has a lot of charm.. it is kinda of hidden but it adds to the beauty. Place is clean, everyone is plateful and caring to give you a good service.

Will come back many times more  and I highly recommend it to anyone with some serious Mexican Munchies!< /review>

< review>
Small place with lots of Goodness. We ate outside, It is beautifully decorated and feels homie. You can hear the water fountain in the background and feel the breeze as you enjoy your amazing food.

Mexican food on point. We had four dishes served. Everything from the Waitress attending to us, to the food was perfect!

5 star for the food.
Had the Grilled Steak Burrito and it was delightful and big.
Also had The Fajitas .. and OMG! Delicious!

My girlfriend had the Chicken enchiladas, and she enjoy how delicious and good it was.
She also had the Shreded Beef Mojado Burrito .. and she said the sauce on it was perfect.. not spicy but good and perfect.

The location is small but has a lot of charm.. it is kinda of hidden but it adds to the beauty. Place is clean, everyone is politeful and caring to give you a good service.

Will come back many times more  and I highly recommend it to anyone with some serious Mexican Munchies!</review>

< UserId.>
102159248456998327459< /UserId.>
<Name>Samuel Scott</Name>< Review>
Pros: quick seating. Good service. Friendly staff. Lots of parking. Cons: Small space. Bathroom not in main area. Food: breakfast burrito(bacon), azteca sopa, Nutella banana crepe, and huevos rancheros. Soup was good but could have used more fillings(tortilla strips, cheese, avocado, etc). Thumbs up for the crepes. Was a nice way to share a dessert and end the meal. Huevos rancheros wasn't what I was expecting.. The tortillas aren't friend so you didn't get that crunch in the bite so it wasn't my cup of tea. Not bad... Just not good. Burrito was ok... Just a burrito.

They put pico de gallo in there so if you don't want that you'll have to let them know. No salsa was offered and everything is mild (even what they say is spicy on menu) so ask them for spicier sauce if you like spicy. If you're looking for dirty authentic Mexican this won't be the spot for you. If you want clean mild sit down Mexican then this is a great spot for you!<//Review>

<GmapID>0x80c288ea0b6bf801:0x46533211f40fef30< /GmapID></record></dataset><record>
< rate>
5< /rate>
< Text>
I am in love with the owners of this business (Albert & Maggie)! They are so welcoming and good hearted people. Customer service is everything to me, and they have that nailed. Each time I visit, I leave feeling so happy. They have so much passion in what they do and genuinely care.

Simply irresistible... my exact thought as I took my first bite of the recommended Chile en Nogada. OMG!

I am not even exaggerating,  this is the best dish I have ever tired and is now my favorite food dish! Each bite literally melted in my mouth. It was sweet, it was salty (the good kind), it was slightly spicy... I can't even describe. If I wasn't being watched I would've licked the sauce off my plate lol. Just try it please.

So me and my love went back for dinner. I ordered the Pozole, he ordered a burrito with shredded beef.

The Pozole was presented in a HUGE bowl with all the extra goodies on the side: shredded lettuce, chopped onions, sliced radishes, lime wedge and crunchy tortillas. I love Pozole sooo much, just so comforting. But I haven't had it in a while because I never order from restaurants, has to be homemade with love. While Ay Caramba's Pozole is exactly that! So thankful for the big serving so I could take the rest home to enjoy later.

My man loves burritos and is super picky too! He typically doesn't get the shredded beef because he has had bad experiences with it being too chewy and too much fat. While that was not a problem this time. It was topped with red sauce and cheese but it was not a messy wet burrito. It had just the right amount for each bite. With each bite he kept talking to himself about how good it was! By the time I  had a chance to take a picture of our meal, his burrito was practically gone (see pic lol).

I also had several cups of horchata. I grew up with my grandma making me "rice water" as I called it. There's is just as yummy!

I highly recommend!!!< /Text>

<Time>1516427428450< /Time>< Rate>

< Text>
Great place to be, greatest people to be around. Interesting and innovative crafts coming out of Covina CA. Has trivia, food trucks and games. I especially recommend trying their sours, some of which truly rank top in my all time list of must-have beers. I especially like that they don't use cheap shortcuts to get taste. They actually brew intelligently to get the flavors they want in their beer. Always love a place that brews without gimmicks. Can't wait to see what new things they roll out for the coming year. (Try their blueberry sour- if you can get it. I'd fist fight a nun in the parking lot for a drop.)

1-19-18
Update: a, new beer out of Alosta to recommend, one of the more interesting I've had out of the Azusa/Covina area lately, Amarillo Wild. Its a mild sour, sweet but tart, floral and refreshing, enough sugar that you can drink 2 or 3 but exemplary balance. If you like sours or beers that are light on the palate, absolutely a must-try.<//Text>

<Response>None</Response><Date>1567751573140< /Date><userid>111940822614113195728< /userid><Gmap_id>0x80d954206d215a19:0x81fba09b3307722d<//Gmap_id><user_name>The Poetry Market</user_name><Text>Happytime Tea is a little gem tucked into this plaza. It has a nice ambience, is very spacious and looks good for hosting small parties and events.

When it comes to the menu, I've tried an assortment of drinks including the Vietnamese iced coffee and Thai iced tea. They're both very flavorful and the coffee hits with a jolt of energy (it's potent). It's also family owned. All in all, the location is easily accessible with ground-level storefront parking.</Text></record>

<Text>This is one of the least responsive dealerships I have ever dealt with. We have purchased five vehicles here in the past 20 years. A Ford aerostar, 3 Ford Fiestas and a Ford focus. With each one, we also purchased extended warranty and maintenance. I realized this does make us the biggest customers in the Ford corporation, but I think it does signify our loyalty as Ford customers. Every time we come for service, they give us a hassle. They claim they can't find our maintenance agreement on their computer or they tell us to make an appointment for a week later. On several occasions over the years, I have gone home to retrieve paperwork to prove I had maintenance agreement. Upon returning to the dealership, I find they somehow discovered it in their system. If this happened once, no problem, anyone can make a mistake. But it happens regularly. Today, I needed a tire replaced, which was covered by my maintenance agreement and extended warranty. The service adviser repeatedly told me I did not have the tires installed here, and I told her I don't take the car anywhere else. Not until the service manager came out and looked up the record in her office did they confirm I had purchased the tires here. I think the dealership intentionally places roadblocks in front of customers to dissuade them from getting the service they have already paid for and deserve. Only people who are willing to push them actually get the service they've paid for.
My advice: avoid this place. There are plenty of places to buy a car.< /Text><username>Michael Towne<//username><gmap_id>0x80c34ca783d3ba43:0xe99450d446163288< /gmap_id><Response>None<//Response><pics>None<//pics>< UserId.>

< review>
In my humble opinion, Chick-fil-A has the best fried chicken recipe of all take out restaurants. Possibly because I have a profound sweet tooth and a penchant for Christian businesses that close on Sundays, their secret ingredient in the batter keeps me coming back for more. üòâ The market salad with a substitution of nuggets for grilled filet with balsamic vinaigrette for the dressing is my favorite "healthy"choice on the menu. The bleu cheese crumbles mixed with the strawberries are the difference maker for me on this entree. My other favorite item on the menu that always gives the cashier/clerk a smirk or a chuckle is the kid's meal 6 piece nugget meal with a diet coke and 1 ketchup packet and 1 chick fil a sauce. I always tell them to keep the kid's toy that is usually included in such "meals" and to substitute for an ice cream cone. Hands down chick fil A has the best soft serve vanilla ice cream in the world. It is so good, that even when it was zero degrees outside in the greater Chicagoland area, when my sweet tooth would hit, off to the drive through I would go for that little treat. Don't judge. Seriously, it's that delicious, plus it's family friendly and they take customer service very seriously with their "my pleasure" and asking for your name instead of giving you a number at the counter.<//review>

< review>

DILLON is a shining example of what service should be!  He is the Schindlers List to the holocaust of poor restaurant experiences.  A new tux in a world of brown shoes.  Tonight I learned the name of my unborn son...his name shall be DILLON....so that maybe one day he too can spread joy throughout the world.  If DILLON started a cult...his koolaid would be spiked with kindness!  I now know what the angels will say when they welcome me home...."Hi, may name is DILLON...how may I serve you today."

Then when we got home after regaling each other with our own personal DILLON experience....I found an extra nugget in my 12 piece meal.  I like to think this was a little special gift from DILLON.< /review>

<user>102604747660888286919< /user><name>Mark D Kennedy< /name><date>1524719117885<//date>< Rating>
5</Rating>
< review>
Today was my first visit to a new place. I was informed by a friendly member of the excellent staff that they have been open since October 2017. This is a great new place. The dining room is huge and has large windows that let in plenty of light and there is even a children's playroom in a separate access area at the far end of the dining area. Perfect for families with children. The restrooms are state of the art and very spacious. There is a red umbrella dining area outside the front end of the building. The Traffic Circle is right across the road from the front of the building and the outside dining area. An excellent location.
I had the Chick Fil-A deluxe with the waffle fries and generous amounts of ice-cold cherry coke and I was, from the first bite, extremely impressed with the uniqueness and quality of the taste and the quality of the ingredients used. I have, over the years, had the chicken from all the other ones, McDonalds, Wendy's, Carls Jr ect..., and I can say that without a doubt that this is the best chicken that I have EVER tasted. Something about how it is prepared, I'm not going to tell you the secret, seals in the flavor and boosts it to the front end of the flavor spectrum. None of the others can hold a candle to this. I will say it again, This is THE BEST chicken I have EVER tasted.
The wonderful staff ply you with refills so you don't have to get it yourself most of the time. None of the others do this and that is another distinction that puts them a cut above the rest right off the bat.
I will most assuredly return again to continue my exploration of the gastronomical delights contained in their substantial menu. If you are reading this, I challenge you to go with THE BEST and to forget all the rest. Why do you want McDonalds when you can have THIS!!!.

Tuesday (4-24-18)
MDK
On my MacBook Pro<//review>

< text>
Today was my first visit to a new place. I was informed by a friendly member of the excellent staff that they have been open since October 2017. This is a great new place. The dining room is huge and has large windows that let in plenty of light and there is even a children's playroom in a separate access area at the far end of the dining area. Perfect for families with children. The restrooms are state of the art and very spacious. There is a red umbrella dining area outside the front end of the building. The Traffic Circle is right across the road from the front of the building and the outside dining area. An excellent location.
I had the Chick Fil-A deluxe with the waffle fries and generous amounts of ice-cold cherry coke and I was, from the first bite, extremely impressed with the uniqueness and quality of the taste and the quality of the ingredients used. I have, over the years, had the chicken from all the other ones, McDonalds, Wendy's, Carls Jr ect..., and I can say that without a doubt that this is the best chicken that I have EVER tasted. Something about how it is prepared, I'm not going to tell you the secret, seals in the flavor and boosts it to the front end of the flavor spectrum. None of the others can hold a candle to this. I will say it again, This is THE BEST chicken I have EVER tasted.
The wonderful staff ply you with refills so you don't have to get it yourself most of the time. None of the others do this and that is another distinction that puts them a cut above the rest right off the bat.
I will most assuredly return again to continue my exploration of the gastronomical delights contained in their substantial menu. If you are reading this, I challenge you to go with THE BEST and to forget all the rest. Why do you want McDonalds when you can have THIS!!!.

Tuesday (4-24-18)
MDK
On my MacBook Pro< /text>
